data.event: Its population as of 2007 was estimated to be 6,600 people living in a total area of 104 square kilometres (40 sq mi).
The main crops were sugarcane (6,000 ha or 15,000 acres planted in 2006) and soybeans (700 ha or 1,700 acres planted in 2006), but oranges, cotton, rice, beans and corn were also grown.
